tested on AMD+AMD+Win7 only

to encode YUV4MPEG2 file:

BINARY_FILE -i input.y4m -o output.ivf -qi 8 -qp 48 -g 350 -w 32768 -t 4 -vx 32 -vy 16 -ll 0 -ls 0

to encode any file pipelining from FFMPEG

ffmpeg -i input.mp4 -f yuv4mpegpipe -pix_fmt yuv420p - | BINARY_FILE -i @ -o demo1.ivf -qi 8 -qp 48 -g 1000 -w 32768 -t 4 -vx 32 -vy 16 -ll 0 -ls 0
